Note:
IEEE 754-2008 Decimal128 (decimal interchange format, 128 bits).

Reference: IEEE Std 754-2008, Section 3.5.2 (decimal interchange formats),
Section 5 (operations), Section 4 (rounding-direction attributes), and
Section 7 (default exception handling).

Format: 128 bits total
    sign        1 bit
    combination 17 bits
    coefficient 110 bits

Significand: 34 decimal digits
Biased exponent range: 0..12287
Exponent bias: 6176
Unbiased exponent range Emax: +6144, Emin: -6143

Encoding selected: BID (Binary Integer Decimal). The 34-digit
coefficient exceeds the 18-digit Integer range, so the in-memory
representation stores the coefficient as a digit buffer (one byte per
digit, MSD at index 0). The encoded BID form uses two 64-bit Integer
words: bits 127..64 in the high word and bits 63..0 in the low word.

Decimal128 is the natural "treasury / sovereign-grade" currency type:
34 decimal digits accommodate quintillions of units with 16+ decimal
places of precision, sufficient for sovereign-scale digital currency
arithmetic at planetary scale and for cross-jurisdiction multi-precision
financial reconciliation.

Unpacked representation:
    Allocated struct (48 bytes):
        offset 0  : sign           (0 = positive, 1 = negative)
        offset 8  : kind           (0 finite, 1 +Inf, 2 -Inf, 3 qNaN, 4 sNaN)
        offset 16 : digits         (pointer to digit buffer; big-endian)
        offset 24 : digit_count    (number of valid digits, no leading zeros)
        offset 32 : exponent       (unbiased decimal exponent)
        offset 40 : reserved       (zero, for future double-word coefficient)

Encoded BID-128 layout uses two Integer slots (low, high) returned as a
pair via output pointer; see dec128_encode_bid.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/numeric/decimal/decimal_bignum.runa" as Bignum

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Constants - IEEE 754-2008 Decimal128 parameters
Note: ============================================================================

Constant DEC128_PRECISION as Integer is 34
Constant DEC128_EMAX as Integer is 6144
Constant DEC128_EMIN as Integer is -6143
Constant DEC128_BIAS as Integer is 6176
Constant DEC128_MAX_BIASED_EXP as Integer is 12287

Constant DEC128_KIND_FINITE as Integer is 0
Constant DEC128_KIND_POS_INF as Integer is 1
Constant DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF as Integer is 2
Constant DEC128_KIND_QNAN as Integer is 3
Constant DEC128_KIND_SNAN as Integer is 4

Constant DEC128_ROUND_HALF_EVEN as Integer is 0
Constant DEC128_ROUND_HALF_UP as Integer is 1
Constant DEC128_ROUND_TOWARD_ZERO as Integer is 2
Constant DEC128_ROUND_TOWARD_POS as Integer is 3
Constant DEC128_ROUND_TOWARD_NEG as Integer is 4

Constant DEC128_UNPACKED_SIZE as Integer is 48

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Unpacked triple constructors / accessors
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_unpacked_create" takes sign as Integer, kind as Integer, digits as Integer, digit_count as Integer, exponent as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocates a 48-byte unpacked struct. The digit buffer is OWNED by
    the unpacked triple from this point on; callers must NOT free it
    independently. dec128_destroy will free both the struct and the
    digit buffer.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Layout.allocate(48) + 5 stores; reserved field zeroed.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Single struct allocation per value. Hot path; consider an arena
    pool for short-lived intermediates in a future optimization.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    On allocation failure we free the supplied digit buffer to avoid
    a double-ownership leak.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let p be Layout.allocate(DEC128_UNPACKED_SIZE)
    If p is equal to 0:
        If digits is not equal to 0:
            Bignum.decbn_free(digits)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    __store(p, 0, sign)
    __store(p, 8, kind)
    __store(p, 16, digits)
    __store(p, 24, digit_count)
    __store(p, 32, exponent)
    __store(p, 40, 0)
    Return p
End Process

Process called "dec128_get_sign" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return __load(p, 0)
End Process

Process called "dec128_get_kind" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return DEC128_KIND_QNAN
    End If
    Return __load(p, 8)
End Process

Process called "dec128_get_digits" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return __load(p, 16)
End Process

Process called "dec128_get_digit_count" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return __load(p, 24)
End Process

Process called "dec128_get_exponent" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return __load(p, 32)
End Process

Process called "dec128_destroy" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Frees both the unpacked struct and its owned digit buffer.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load digit pointer, free it, free struct.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Double-free triggers canary protocol.
    @End Security_Scope

    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let digits be __load(p, 16)
    If digits is not equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(digits)
    End If
    Layout.deallocate(p)
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Special-value constructors
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_make_zero" takes sign as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Signed zero with preferred exponent 0.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Allocate a single-digit buffer holding 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two allocations.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    sign normalized to 0/1.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let s be sign
    If s is not equal to 0:
        Set s to 1
    End If
    Let buf be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, 0, 0)
    Return dec128_unpacked_create(s, DEC128_KIND_FINITE, buf, 1, 0)
End Process

Process called "dec128_make_infinity" takes sign as Integer returns Integer:
    Let s be sign
    If s is not equal to 0:
        Set s to 1
    End If
    Let k be DEC128_KIND_POS_INF
    If s is equal to 1:
        Set k to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF
    End If
    Return dec128_unpacked_create(s, k, 0, 0, 0)
End Process

Process called "dec128_make_qnan" returns Integer:
    Return dec128_unpacked_create(0, DEC128_KIND_QNAN, 0, 0, 0)
End Process

Process called "dec128_make_snan" returns Integer:
    Return dec128_unpacked_create(0, DEC128_KIND_SNAN, 0, 0, 0)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Predicates
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_is_zero" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If __load(p, 8) is not equal to DEC128_KIND_FINITE:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dc be __load(p, 24)
    If dc is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let digits be __load(p, 16)
    If digits is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than dc:
        If Memory.memory_get_byte(digits, i) is not equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "dec128_is_finite" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If __load(p, 8) is equal to DEC128_KIND_FINITE:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "dec128_is_infinite" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let k be __load(p, 8)
    If k is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        Return 1
    End If
    If k is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "dec128_is_nan" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let k be __load(p, 8)
    If k is equal to DEC128_KIND_QNAN:
        Return 1
    End If
    If k is equal to DEC128_KIND_SNAN:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "dec128_is_signaling" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If __load(p, 8) is equal to DEC128_KIND_SNAN:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "dec128_is_negative" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If __load(p, 0) is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "dec128_propagate_nan" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    IEEE 754-2008 Section 6.2 NaN propagation: sNaN -> qNaN with
    invalid signal; otherwise qNaN if any operand qNaN.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Check sNaN then qNaN.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Hot path.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is not equal to 0:
        If __load(a, 8) is equal to DEC128_KIND_SNAN:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
    End If
    If b is not equal to 0:
        If __load(b, 8) is equal to DEC128_KIND_SNAN:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
    End If
    If a is not equal to 0:
        If __load(a, 8) is equal to DEC128_KIND_QNAN:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
    End If
    If b is not equal to 0:
        If __load(b, 8) is equal to DEC128_KIND_QNAN:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Helper: ensure the digit buffer is normalized (no leading zeros)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_normalize" takes digits as Integer, digit_count as Integer, out_count_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns a fresh digit buffer with leading zeros stripped. If the
    input is all zeros, returns a single-digit zero buffer.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Find first non-zero index; copy from there.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(digit_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If digits is equal to 0:
        Let zero be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
        If zero is equal to 0:
            If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
                __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zero, 0, 0)
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 1)
        End If
        Return zero
    End If
    Let first_nz be 0
    Let scanning be 1
    While scanning is equal to 1:
        If first_nz is greater than or equal to digit_count minus 1:
            Set scanning to 0
        Otherwise:
            If Memory.memory_get_byte(digits, first_nz) is equal to 0:
                Set first_nz to first_nz plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set scanning to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Let new_count be digit_count minus first_nz
    Let buf be Bignum.decbn_alloc(new_count plus 1)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than new_count:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, i, Memory.memory_get_byte(digits, first_nz plus i))
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
        __store(out_count_ptr, 0, new_count)
    End If
    Return buf
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Round to precision
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_round_finite" takes sign as Integer, digits as Integer, digit_count as Integer, exp as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Brings a finite digit buffer into the 34-digit precision window
    per IEEE 754-2008 Section 4.3, then clamps the exponent into
    [DEC128_EMIN, DEC128_EMAX] with overflow-to-infinity / underflow-to-
    zero semantics per Section 7.4.

    NOTE: This function ASSUMES OWNERSHIP of the supplied digit buffer.
    On any path that returns a different buffer, the input must be
    freed. We document this strongly because the alternative
    (always-copy) would double the allocation cost.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. If digit_count is 0 or buffer is zero, treat as exact zero.
    2. Strip leading zeros first (normalize).
    3. Call decbn_round_to_precision for the digit-domain rounding.
    4. Apply exponent overflow/underflow clamps.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(digit_count + excess).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Pure aside from final allocations.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let s be sign
    If s is not equal to 0:
        Set s to 1
    End If

    Let norm_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If norm_count_ptr is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(digits)
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Let norm_digits be dec128_normalize(digits, digit_count, norm_count_ptr)
    Let norm_count be __load(norm_count_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(norm_count_ptr)
    Bignum.decbn_free(digits)
    If norm_digits is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Note: Check if buffer represents zero.
    Let is_zero be 1
    Let scan_i be 0
    While scan_i is less than norm_count:
        If Memory.memory_get_byte(norm_digits, scan_i) is not equal to 0:
            Set is_zero to 0
            Set scan_i to norm_count
        Otherwise:
            Set scan_i to scan_i plus 1
        End If
    End While
    If is_zero is equal to 1:
        Let ez be exp
        If ez is greater than DEC128_EMAX:
            Set ez to DEC128_EMAX
        End If
        If ez is less than DEC128_EMIN:
            Set ez to DEC128_EMIN
        End If
        Note: Replace with canonical zero buffer.
        Bignum.decbn_free(norm_digits)
        Let zb be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
        If zb is equal to 0:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zb, 0, 0)
        Return dec128_unpacked_create(s, DEC128_KIND_FINITE, zb, 1, ez)
    End If

    Let rounded_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    Let exp_delta_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If rounded_count_ptr is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(norm_digits)
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    If exp_delta_ptr is equal to 0:
        Layout.deallocate(rounded_count_ptr)
        Bignum.decbn_free(norm_digits)
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Let rounded be Bignum.decbn_round_to_precision(norm_digits, norm_count, DEC128_PRECISION, s, rounding_mode, rounded_count_ptr, exp_delta_ptr)
    Let rounded_count be __load(rounded_count_ptr, 0)
    Let exp_delta be __load(exp_delta_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(rounded_count_ptr)
    Layout.deallocate(exp_delta_ptr)
    Bignum.decbn_free(norm_digits)
    If rounded is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Let final_exp be exp plus exp_delta

    If final_exp is greater than DEC128_EMAX:
        Note: Try to absorb the overflow into trailing zeros of the
        Note: coefficient, but only while the digit count stays within
        Note: DEC128_PRECISION.
        While final_exp is greater than DEC128_EMAX:
            If rounded_count is greater than or equal to DEC128_PRECISION:
                Bignum.decbn_free(rounded)
                Return dec128_make_infinity(s)
            End If
            Note: Append a trailing zero: increment digit count.
            Memory.memory_set_byte(rounded, rounded_count, 0)
            Set rounded_count to rounded_count plus 1
            Set final_exp to final_exp minus 1
        End While
    End If

    If final_exp is less than DEC128_EMIN:
        Note: Subnormal: shift the buffer right (with rounding) until
        Note: exponent is in range.
        While final_exp is less than DEC128_EMIN:
            If rounded_count is equal to 0:
                Note: Underflow to zero.
                Bignum.decbn_free(rounded)
                Let zb2 be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
                If zb2 is equal to 0:
                    Return dec128_make_qnan()
                End If
                Memory.memory_set_byte(zb2, 0, 0)
                Return dec128_unpacked_create(s, DEC128_KIND_FINITE, zb2, 1, DEC128_EMIN)
            End If
            Let last_d be Memory.memory_get_byte(rounded, rounded_count minus 1)
            Set rounded_count to rounded_count minus 1
            Let rup be 0
            If rounding_mode is equal to DEC128_ROUND_HALF_EVEN:
                If last_d is greater than 5:
                    Set rup to 1
                Otherwise:
                    If last_d is equal to 5:
                        If rounded_count is greater than 0:
                            Let new_last be Memory.memory_get_byte(rounded, rounded_count minus 1)
                            If new_last is not equal to ((new_last divided by 2) multiplied by 2):
                                Set rup to 1
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            If rounding_mode is equal to DEC128_ROUND_HALF_UP:
                If last_d is greater than or equal to 5:
                    Set rup to 1
                End If
            End If
            If rounding_mode is equal to DEC128_ROUND_TOWARD_POS:
                If s is equal to 0:
                    If last_d is greater than 0:
                        Set rup to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            If rounding_mode is equal to DEC128_ROUND_TOWARD_NEG:
                If s is equal to 1:
                    If last_d is greater than 0:
                        Set rup to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            If rup is equal to 1:
                Let carry be 1
                Let cp be rounded_count minus 1
                While cp is greater than or equal to 0:
                    If carry is equal to 0:
                        Set cp to -1
                    Otherwise:
                        Let d be Memory.memory_get_byte(rounded, cp)
                        Set d to d plus 1
                        If d is equal to 10:
                            Memory.memory_set_byte(rounded, cp, 0)
                            Set carry to 1
                        Otherwise:
                            Memory.memory_set_byte(rounded, cp, d)
                            Set carry to 0
                        End If
                        Set cp to cp minus 1
                    End If
                End While
                If carry is equal to 1:
                    Let r2 be rounded_count minus 1
                    While r2 is greater than or equal to 0:
                        Memory.memory_set_byte(rounded, r2 plus 1, Memory.memory_get_byte(rounded, r2))
                        Set r2 to r2 minus 1
                    End While
                    Memory.memory_set_byte(rounded, 0, 1)
                    Set rounded_count to rounded_count plus 1
                End If
            End If
            Set final_exp to final_exp plus 1
        End While
    End If

    If rounded_count is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(rounded)
        Let zb3 be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
        If zb3 is equal to 0:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zb3, 0, 0)
        Return dec128_unpacked_create(s, DEC128_KIND_FINITE, zb3, 1, final_exp)
    End If

    Return dec128_unpacked_create(s, DEC128_KIND_FINITE, rounded, rounded_count, final_exp)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Comparison
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_compare" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Three-way compare with NaN unordered sentinel (-2). Same semantics
    as Decimal{32,64}.compare.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    NaN handling; Inf handling; sign-aware magnitude compare with
    exponent alignment in the digit-buffer domain.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Best case O(1) for sign-differing operands; worst case O(digit
    count + |exp diff|).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Pure aside from temporary allocations during alignment. Allocation
    failure returns -2.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is equal to 0:
        Return -2
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return -2
    End If
    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let kb be __load(b, 8)
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_QNAN:
        Return -2
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_SNAN:
        Return -2
    End If
    If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_QNAN:
        Return -2
    End If
    If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_SNAN:
        Return -2
    End If

    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return -1
    End If
    If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        Return -1
    End If
    If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let sb be __load(b, 0)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let eb be __load(b, 32)
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let db be __load(b, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let dcb be __load(b, 24)

    Let a_zero be dec128_is_zero(a)
    Let b_zero be dec128_is_zero(b)
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        If b_zero is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    If sa is not equal to sb:
        If a_zero is equal to 1:
            If b_zero is equal to 1:
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
        If sa is equal to 1:
            Return -1
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Same sign: align exponents to the smaller, scale up the
    Note: higher-exponent operand by appending zeros to its digit
    Note: buffer, then compare magnitudes.
    Let exp_common be ea
    If eb is less than ea:
        Set exp_common to eb
    End If
    Let shift_a be ea minus exp_common
    Let shift_b be eb minus exp_common

    Let scaled_a_count be dca plus shift_a
    Let scaled_b_count be dcb plus shift_b
    Let scaled_a be Bignum.decbn_alloc(scaled_a_count plus 1)
    If scaled_a is equal to 0:
        Return -2
    End If
    Let scaled_b be Bignum.decbn_alloc(scaled_b_count plus 1)
    If scaled_b is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_a)
        Return -2
    End If

    Let ai be 0
    While ai is less than dca:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_a, ai, Memory.memory_get_byte(da, ai))
        Set ai to ai plus 1
    End While
    Let azi be 0
    While azi is less than shift_a:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_a, dca plus azi, 0)
        Set azi to azi plus 1
    End While

    Let bi be 0
    While bi is less than dcb:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_b, bi, Memory.memory_get_byte(db, bi))
        Set bi to bi plus 1
    End While
    Let bzi be 0
    While bzi is less than shift_b:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_b, dcb plus bzi, 0)
        Set bzi to bzi plus 1
    End While

    Let cmp be Bignum.decbn_compare_magnitude(scaled_a, scaled_a_count, scaled_b, scaled_b_count)
    Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_a)
    Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_b)

    If sa is equal to 1:
        Return 0 minus cmp
    End If
    Return cmp
End Process

Process called "dec128_eq" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be dec128_compare(a, b)
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "dec128_ne" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be dec128_compare(a, b)
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "dec128_lt" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be dec128_compare(a, b)
    If c is equal to -1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "dec128_le" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be dec128_compare(a, b)
    If c is equal to -1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "dec128_gt" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be dec128_compare(a, b)
    If c is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "dec128_ge" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be dec128_compare(a, b)
    If c is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Negation, abs
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_neg" takes a as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bit-level sign flip; preserves digit buffer and exponent.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Copy digit buffer; flip sign and kind for infinities.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One digit-buffer copy plus one struct allocation.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let new_sign be 1
    If sa is equal to 1:
        Set new_sign to 0
    End If
    Let new_kind be ka
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set new_kind to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set new_kind to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF
    End If
    Let copy_digits be 0
    If da is not equal to 0:
        Set copy_digits to Bignum.decbn_copy(da, dca)
        If copy_digits is equal to 0:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
    End If
    Return dec128_unpacked_create(new_sign, new_kind, copy_digits, dca, ea)
End Process

Process called "dec128_abs_value" takes a as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bit-level sign clear.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Sign 0; preserve everything else; NEG_INF -> POS_INF.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One digit-buffer copy.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let new_kind be ka
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set new_kind to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF
    End If
    Let copy_digits be 0
    If da is not equal to 0:
        Set copy_digits to Bignum.decbn_copy(da, dca)
        If copy_digits is equal to 0:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
    End If
    Return dec128_unpacked_create(0, new_kind, copy_digits, dca, ea)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Addition / subtraction in the digit-buffer domain
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_add" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Decimal128 addition. Align both digit buffers to the smaller
    exponent by appending zeros to the higher-exponent operand, then
    add or subtract magnitudes in the digit-buffer domain with
    sign-aware combination. Round once to DEC128_PRECISION.

    Correctness: For exact representable inputs whose sum fits in 34
    digits, the result is bit-exact. This guarantees the canonical
    "0.1 + 0.2 = 0.3" at Decimal128 precision.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. NaN propagation; Inf handling.
    2. Zero pad both operands to the common exponent.
    3. If signs match: decbn_add_magnitude.
       Else: compare magnitudes, decbn_sub_magnitude with the larger
       in front, result sign = sign of the larger operand.
    4. dec128_round_finite to finalize.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Alignment may scale up to ~70 digits in pathological cases; for
    finance the typical diff is small.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Inf + (-Inf) = qNaN invalid.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let np be dec128_propagate_nan(a, b)
    If np is not equal to 0:
        Return np
    End If
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let kb be __load(b, 8)

    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Return dec128_make_infinity(0)
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Return dec128_make_infinity(1)
    End If
    If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        Return dec128_make_infinity(0)
    End If
    If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Return dec128_make_infinity(1)
    End If

    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let sb be __load(b, 0)
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let db be __load(b, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let dcb be __load(b, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let eb be __load(b, 32)

    Note: Align both operands to a single exp_common. The natural choice
    Note: is min(ea, eb), but the larger-magnitude operand would then
    Note: require scaling up by (max-min) digits. To bound the buffer
    Note: size we cap that upward scale at max_shift = DEC128_PRECISION
    Note: + 2 = 36 digits. When the gap exceeds the cap we re-anchor
    Note: exp_common UP to max(ea,eb) - max_shift; the larger operand
    Note: then scales by exactly max_shift digits and the smaller operand
    Note: scales DOWN, with any discarded digits captured as a sticky
    Note: bit that biases the final round per IEEE 754-2008 §4.3.
    Let max_shift be DEC128_PRECISION plus 2
    Let exp_common be ea
    If eb is less than ea:
        Set exp_common to eb
    End If
    Let raw_shift_a be ea minus exp_common
    Let raw_shift_b be eb minus exp_common
    If raw_shift_a is greater than max_shift:
        Set exp_common to ea minus max_shift
    End If
    If raw_shift_b is greater than max_shift:
        Set exp_common to eb minus max_shift
    End If
    Let shift_a be ea minus exp_common
    Let shift_b be eb minus exp_common

    Note: Determine how many trailing digits of each operand fall below
    Note: exp_common. A negative shift means the operand needs to be
    Note: divided by 10^|shift| with any discarded digit setting sticky.
    Let drop_a be 0
    If shift_a is less than 0:
        Set drop_a to 0 minus shift_a
    End If
    Let drop_b be 0
    If shift_b is less than 0:
        Set drop_b to 0 minus shift_b
    End If

    Let kept_a be dca minus drop_a
    If kept_a is less than 0:
        Set kept_a to 0
    End If
    Let kept_b be dcb minus drop_b
    If kept_b is less than 0:
        Set kept_b to 0
    End If

    Let sticky_a be 0
    If drop_a is greater than 0:
        Let scan_a be kept_a
        While scan_a is less than dca:
            If Memory.memory_get_byte(da, scan_a) is not equal to 0:
                Set sticky_a to 1
                Set scan_a to dca
            Otherwise:
                Set scan_a to scan_a plus 1
            End If
        End While
    End If
    Let sticky_b be 0
    If drop_b is greater than 0:
        Let scan_b be kept_b
        While scan_b is less than dcb:
            If Memory.memory_get_byte(db, scan_b) is not equal to 0:
                Set sticky_b to 1
                Set scan_b to dcb
            Otherwise:
                Set scan_b to scan_b plus 1
            End If
        End While
    End If

    Note: scaled_X holds the operand's kept digits followed by
    Note: max(0, shift_X) zeros so the aligned magnitude sits at
    Note: exp_common. The kept digit count is whichever of dca/dcb
    Note: survived the drop; zero-pad count is max(shift, 0).
    Let pad_a be shift_a
    If pad_a is less than 0:
        Set pad_a to 0
    End If
    Let pad_b be shift_b
    If pad_b is less than 0:
        Set pad_b to 0
    End If
    Let scaled_a_count be kept_a plus pad_a
    Let scaled_b_count be kept_b plus pad_b
    If scaled_a_count is equal to 0:
        Set scaled_a_count to 1
    End If
    If scaled_b_count is equal to 0:
        Set scaled_b_count to 1
    End If

    Let scaled_a be Bignum.decbn_alloc(scaled_a_count plus 1)
    If scaled_a is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Let scaled_b be Bignum.decbn_alloc(scaled_b_count plus 1)
    If scaled_b is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_a)
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Let init_a be 0
    While init_a is less than (scaled_a_count plus 1):
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_a, init_a, 0)
        Set init_a to init_a plus 1
    End While
    Let init_b be 0
    While init_b is less than (scaled_b_count plus 1):
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_b, init_b, 0)
        Set init_b to init_b plus 1
    End While

    Let ai be 0
    While ai is less than kept_a:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_a, ai, Memory.memory_get_byte(da, ai))
        Set ai to ai plus 1
    End While
    Let az be 0
    While az is less than pad_a:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_a, kept_a plus az, 0)
        Set az to az plus 1
    End While

    Let bi be 0
    While bi is less than kept_b:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_b, bi, Memory.memory_get_byte(db, bi))
        Set bi to bi plus 1
    End While
    Let bz be 0
    While bz is less than pad_b:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_b, kept_b plus bz, 0)
        Set bz to bz plus 1
    End While

    Let result_sign be 0
    Let combined_buf be 0
    Let combined_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If combined_count_ptr is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_a)
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_b)
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Let combined_sticky be sticky_a bitwise or sticky_b
    Let cancel_borrow be 0
    If sa is equal to sb:
        Set combined_buf to Bignum.decbn_add_magnitude(scaled_a, scaled_a_count, scaled_b, scaled_b_count, combined_count_ptr)
        Set result_sign to sa
    Otherwise:
        Let cmp be Bignum.decbn_compare_magnitude(scaled_a, scaled_a_count, scaled_b, scaled_b_count)
        If cmp is greater than 0:
            Set combined_buf to Bignum.decbn_sub_magnitude(scaled_a, scaled_a_count, scaled_b, scaled_b_count, combined_count_ptr)
            Set result_sign to sa
            Note: The true |B| equals scaled_b plus an epsilon of value
            Note: less than one ULP at exp_common (the discarded sticky
            Note: tail). The true A - B therefore lies strictly less
            Note: than the integer (scaled_a - scaled_b). Decrement the
            Note: difference by one ULP and flag sticky so the rounder
            Note: knows the true value sits between (result-1, result).
            If sticky_b is not equal to 0:
                Set cancel_borrow to 1
            End If
        End If
        If cmp is less than 0:
            Set combined_buf to Bignum.decbn_sub_magnitude(scaled_b, scaled_b_count, scaled_a, scaled_a_count, combined_count_ptr)
            Set result_sign to sb
            If sticky_a is not equal to 0:
                Set cancel_borrow to 1
            End If
        End If
        If cmp is equal to 0:
            Let zb be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
            If zb is equal to 0:
                Layout.deallocate(combined_count_ptr)
                Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_a)
                Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_b)
                Return dec128_make_qnan()
            End If
            Memory.memory_set_byte(zb, 0, 0)
            Set combined_buf to zb
            __store(combined_count_ptr, 0, 1)
            Note: Equal magnitudes with opposite signs cancel to zero,
            Note: but if only one operand carried a sticky tail the
            Note: TRUE difference is sub-ULP nonzero with the sign of
            Note: the sticky-bearing operand. IEEE 754-2008 §6.3 also
            Note: requires roundTowardNegative to produce -0 on exact
            Note: cancellation.
            If rounding_mode is equal to DEC128_ROUND_TOWARD_NEG:
                Set result_sign to 1
            Otherwise:
                Set result_sign to 0
            End If
            If sticky_a is not equal to 0:
                If sticky_b is equal to 0:
                    Set result_sign to sa
                    Set combined_sticky to 1
                End If
            End If
            If sticky_b is not equal to 0:
                If sticky_a is equal to 0:
                    Set result_sign to sb
                    Set combined_sticky to 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Let combined_count be __load(combined_count_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(combined_count_ptr)
    Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_a)
    Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_b)

    If combined_buf is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Note: Apply the cancel borrow (true A-B is one ULP less than the
    Note: integer difference shown). Propagate -1 through the bignum
    Note: from the LSD with borrow. The buffer is MSD-first so the LSD
    Note: lives at index combined_count - 1.
    If cancel_borrow is equal to 1:
        If combined_count is greater than 0:
            Let bp be combined_count minus 1
            Let borrow be 1
            While bp is greater than or equal to 0:
                If borrow is equal to 0:
                    Set bp to -1
                Otherwise:
                    Let bd be Memory.memory_get_byte(combined_buf, bp)
                    If bd is greater than 0:
                        Memory.memory_set_byte(combined_buf, bp, bd minus 1)
                        Set borrow to 0
                    Otherwise:
                        Memory.memory_set_byte(combined_buf, bp, 9)
                        Set borrow to 1
                    End If
                    Set bp to bp minus 1
                End If
            End While
            Set combined_sticky to 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: Inject combined sticky as a trailing low-order digit so the
    Note: precision-rounding step sees the non-zero residue. Pad the
    Note: buffer to DEC128_PRECISION digits first (so the appended
    Note: sticky lands strictly below the rounding digit), then append
    Note: a '1' digit and decrement exp_common by one for each
    Note: introduced position. This matches the dec32 / dec64
    Note: sticky-injection pattern.
    If combined_sticky is not equal to 0:
        Let need_count be DEC128_PRECISION
        If combined_count is less than need_count:
            Let new_capacity be need_count plus 2
            Let bigger be Bignum.decbn_alloc(new_capacity)
            If bigger is equal to 0:
                Bignum.decbn_free(combined_buf)
                Return dec128_make_qnan()
            End If
            Let ci be 0
            While ci is less than combined_count:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(bigger, ci, Memory.memory_get_byte(combined_buf, ci))
                Set ci to ci plus 1
            End While
            Let pad_z be 0
            While pad_z is less than (need_count minus combined_count):
                Memory.memory_set_byte(bigger, combined_count plus pad_z, 0)
                Set pad_z to pad_z plus 1
            End While
            Let pad_amt be need_count minus combined_count
            Bignum.decbn_free(combined_buf)
            Set combined_buf to bigger
            Set combined_count to need_count
            Set exp_common to exp_common minus pad_amt
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(combined_buf, combined_count, 1)
        Set combined_count to combined_count plus 1
        Set exp_common to exp_common minus 1
    End If

    Return dec128_round_finite(result_sign, combined_buf, combined_count, exp_common, rounding_mode)
End Process

Process called "dec128_sub" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Defined as a + (-b) per IEEE 754-2008.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Negate b, delegate to add.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    One extra struct allocation versus a direct subtract.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Same NaN/Inf semantics as add.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let neg_b be dec128_neg(b, rounding_mode)
    If neg_b is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Let result be dec128_add(a, neg_b, rounding_mode)
    dec128_destroy(neg_b)
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Multiplication
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_mul" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Multiplication via digit-buffer grade-school multiply, then round
    to DEC128_PRECISION. The intermediate product can have up to
    2 * DEC128_PRECISION = 68 digits, all handled in the digit-buffer
    domain.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. NaN/Inf/zero special cases.
    2. Compute coefficient product via decbn_mul.
    3. Add exponents.
    4. Round to precision via dec128_round_finite.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(precision^2) = ~1156 single-digit multiplies plus carries for
    Decimal128.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Inf * 0 -> qNaN. Allocation failure -> qNaN.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let np be dec128_propagate_nan(a, b)
    If np is not equal to 0:
        Return np
    End If
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let kb be __load(b, 8)
    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let sb be __load(b, 0)

    Let result_sign be 0
    If sa is not equal to sb:
        Set result_sign to 1
    End If

    Let a_inf be 0
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set a_inf to 1
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set a_inf to 1
    End If
    Let b_inf be 0
    If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set b_inf to 1
    End If
    If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set b_inf to 1
    End If

    Let a_zero be dec128_is_zero(a)
    Let b_zero be dec128_is_zero(b)

    If a_inf is equal to 1:
        If b_zero is equal to 1:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Return dec128_make_infinity(result_sign)
    End If
    If b_inf is equal to 1:
        If a_zero is equal to 1:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Return dec128_make_infinity(result_sign)
    End If

    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let db be __load(b, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let dcb be __load(b, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let eb be __load(b, 32)
    Let exp_sum be ea plus eb

    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        Let zb be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
        If zb is equal to 0:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zb, 0, 0)
        Return dec128_unpacked_create(result_sign, DEC128_KIND_FINITE, zb, 1, exp_sum)
    End If
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        Let zb2 be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
        If zb2 is equal to 0:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zb2, 0, 0)
        Return dec128_unpacked_create(result_sign, DEC128_KIND_FINITE, zb2, 1, exp_sum)
    End If

    Let prod_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If prod_count_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Let prod be Bignum.decbn_mul(da, dca, db, dcb, prod_count_ptr)
    Let prod_count be __load(prod_count_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(prod_count_ptr)
    If prod is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Return dec128_round_finite(result_sign, prod, prod_count, exp_sum, rounding_mode)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Division
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_div" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Decimal128 division. We scale the dividend by 10^(PRECISION+1) =
    10^35 digits (35 zero digits appended to the digit buffer), divide
    via decbn_div_mod, OR a sticky bit into the quotient's last digit
    if the remainder is non-zero, then round to PRECISION.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. NaN/Inf/zero special cases.
    2. Append (PRECISION+1) zero digits to ca's buffer.
    3. decbn_div_mod.
    4. Sticky-bit OR if remainder non-zero.
    5. Round to PRECISION.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Division is the heaviest operation. ~35 * 34 * 10 = 11900
    digit-level operations.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Division by zero with non-zero dividend signals divideByZero;
    we return signed infinity.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let np be dec128_propagate_nan(a, b)
    If np is not equal to 0:
        Return np
    End If
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let kb be __load(b, 8)
    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let sb be __load(b, 0)
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let db be __load(b, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let dcb be __load(b, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let eb be __load(b, 32)

    Let result_sign be 0
    If sa is not equal to sb:
        Set result_sign to 1
    End If

    Let a_inf be 0
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set a_inf to 1
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set a_inf to 1
    End If
    Let b_inf be 0
    If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set b_inf to 1
    End If
    If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set b_inf to 1
    End If

    If a_inf is equal to 1:
        If b_inf is equal to 1:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Return dec128_make_infinity(result_sign)
    End If
    If b_inf is equal to 1:
        Let zb be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
        If zb is equal to 0:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zb, 0, 0)
        Return dec128_unpacked_create(result_sign, DEC128_KIND_FINITE, zb, 1, 0)
    End If

    Let a_zero be dec128_is_zero(a)
    Let b_zero be dec128_is_zero(b)
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        If a_zero is equal to 1:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Return dec128_make_infinity(result_sign)
    End If
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        Let zb2 be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
        If zb2 is equal to 0:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zb2, 0, 0)
        Return dec128_unpacked_create(result_sign, DEC128_KIND_FINITE, zb2, 1, ea minus eb)
    End If

    Let guard_digits be DEC128_PRECISION plus 1
    Let scaled_count be dca plus guard_digits
    Let scaled be Bignum.decbn_alloc(scaled_count plus 1)
    If scaled is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Let si be 0
    While si is less than dca:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled, si, Memory.memory_get_byte(da, si))
        Set si to si plus 1
    End While
    Let zi be 0
    While zi is less than guard_digits:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled, dca plus zi, 0)
        Set zi to zi plus 1
    End While

    Let q_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    Let r_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    Let r_out_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If q_count_ptr is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    If r_count_ptr is equal to 0:
        Layout.deallocate(q_count_ptr)
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    If r_out_ptr is equal to 0:
        Layout.deallocate(q_count_ptr)
        Layout.deallocate(r_count_ptr)
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    __store(r_out_ptr, 0, 0)

    Let q_buf be Bignum.decbn_div_mod(scaled, scaled_count, db, dcb, q_count_ptr, r_count_ptr, r_out_ptr)
    Let q_count be __load(q_count_ptr, 0)
    Let r_count be __load(r_count_ptr, 0)
    Let rem_buf be __load(r_out_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(q_count_ptr)
    Layout.deallocate(r_count_ptr)
    Layout.deallocate(r_out_ptr)
    Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
    If q_buf is equal to 0:
        If rem_buf is not equal to 0:
            Bignum.decbn_free(rem_buf)
        End If
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Let rem_nonzero be 0
    Let rni be 0
    While rni is less than r_count:
        If Memory.memory_get_byte(rem_buf, rni) is not equal to 0:
            Set rem_nonzero to 1
            Set rni to r_count
        Otherwise:
            Set rni to rni plus 1
        End If
    End While
    If rem_buf is not equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(rem_buf)
    End If
    If rem_nonzero is equal to 1:
        Let last_q be Memory.memory_get_byte(q_buf, q_count minus 1)
        If last_q is equal to ((last_q divided by 2) multiplied by 2):
            Memory.memory_set_byte(q_buf, q_count minus 1, last_q plus 1)
        End If
    End If

    Let final_exp be ea minus eb minus guard_digits
    Return dec128_round_finite(result_sign, q_buf, q_count, final_exp, rounding_mode)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Fused multiply-add
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_fma" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, c as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    FMA per IEEE 754-2008 Section 5.4.1: (a * b) + c with a single
    correctly-rounded result. The product is computed exactly in the
    digit-buffer domain and added to c with proper exponent alignment.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. NaN propagation across a, b, c.
    2. Inf handling across all three operand combinations.
    3. Compute exact product via decbn_mul.
    4. Wrap product as a Decimal128, then dec128_add with c, but with
       the rounding step deferred until after the addition (the
       intermediate Decimal128 result of decbn_mul lives at higher
       precision than DEC128_PRECISION until the final round).

    Single-rounding semantics: the product is computed without
    intermediate rounding (held in unpacked form at its natural digit
    count, up to 68 digits) and then dec128_add applies the user's
    rounding mode. The add path's round_finite reduces the result back
    to DEC128_PRECISION in exactly one rounding step.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    One large mul + one add. Heavier than mul+add when measured by
    cycles, but produces the IEEE 754-2008 correctly-rounded result.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Inf * 0 + anything -> qNaN; Inf*finite + opposite-Inf -> qNaN.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let np_ab be dec128_propagate_nan(a, b)
    If np_ab is not equal to 0:
        Return np_ab
    End If
    Let np_c be dec128_propagate_nan(c, c)
    If np_c is not equal to 0:
        Return np_c
    End If
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let kb be __load(b, 8)
    Let kc be __load(c, 8)
    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let sb be __load(b, 0)
    Let sc be __load(c, 0)

    Let sign_p be 0
    If sa is not equal to sb:
        Set sign_p to 1
    End If

    Let a_inf be 0
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set a_inf to 1
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set a_inf to 1
    End If
    Let b_inf be 0
    If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set b_inf to 1
    End If
    If kb is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set b_inf to 1
    End If
    Let c_inf be 0
    If kc is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set c_inf to 1
    End If
    If kc is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set c_inf to 1
    End If

    Let a_zero be dec128_is_zero(a)
    Let b_zero be dec128_is_zero(b)

    Let prod_is_inf be 0
    If a_inf is equal to 1:
        If b_zero is equal to 1:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Set prod_is_inf to 1
    End If
    If b_inf is equal to 1:
        If a_zero is equal to 1:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Set prod_is_inf to 1
    End If

    If prod_is_inf is equal to 1:
        If c_inf is equal to 1:
            If sc is not equal to sign_p:
                Return dec128_make_qnan()
            End If
        End If
        Return dec128_make_infinity(sign_p)
    End If
    If c_inf is equal to 1:
        Return dec128_make_infinity(sc)
    End If

    Note: All finite. We compute the exact product as an unrounded
    Note: Decimal128 (its digit buffer may be up to 68 digits), then
    Note: dec128_add reduces in a single rounding step. The "single
    Note: rounding" property is preserved because the product itself
    Note: is exact in the digit-buffer domain.
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let db be __load(b, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let dcb be __load(b, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let eb be __load(b, 32)
    Let exp_sum be ea plus eb

    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        Note: 0 * b + c = c. Just return c (copy).
        Return dec128_neg(dec128_neg(c, rounding_mode), rounding_mode)
    End If
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        Return dec128_neg(dec128_neg(c, rounding_mode), rounding_mode)
    End If

    Let prod_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If prod_count_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Let prod be Bignum.decbn_mul(da, dca, db, dcb, prod_count_ptr)
    Let prod_count be __load(prod_count_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(prod_count_ptr)
    If prod is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Note: Wrap the exact product as an UNROUNDED Decimal128. We use
    Note: dec128_unpacked_create directly, skipping the precision
    Note: cap, because dec128_add will reduce in its final round.
    Let exact_prod be dec128_unpacked_create(sign_p, DEC128_KIND_FINITE, prod, prod_count, exp_sum)
    If exact_prod is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(prod)
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Let result be dec128_add(exact_prod, c, rounding_mode)
    dec128_destroy(exact_prod)
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Square root via digit-buffer Newton iteration
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_sqrt" takes a as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Decimal128 sqrt: scale up to ~2*PRECISION digits with even-exponent
    constraint, then compute integer sqrt via digit-buffer Newton.

    For Decimal128 the scaled coefficient is ~68 digits which we
    cannot hold in Integer. The Newton iteration runs in the
    digit-buffer domain using decbn_add_magnitude and decbn_div_mod.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Sign / NaN / Inf / zero special cases.
    2. Scale up to >= 68 digits with even exponent.
    3. Newton iteration: x_new = (x + scaled / x) / 2 (digit-buffer).
    4. Determine round-up via 4*scaled vs (2*x+1)^2 (digit-buffer).
    5. Halve exponent; round.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Iteration converges in ~7 rounds for 68-digit input. Each round
    is a digit-buffer divide.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Negative input -> qNaN with invalid-operation.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_QNAN:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_SNAN:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)

    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        Return dec128_make_infinity(0)
    End If

    If dec128_is_zero(a) is equal to 1:
        Let zb be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
        If zb is equal to 0:
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zb, 0, 0)
        Return dec128_unpacked_create(sa, DEC128_KIND_FINITE, zb, 1, ea divided by 2)
    End If

    If sa is equal to 1:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Note: Scale up to 68 digits.
    Let target_digits be DEC128_PRECISION multiplied by 2
    Let scaled_count be dca
    Let scaled_exp be ea
    Note: First scale by appending 2 zeros at a time until we reach target.
    Let scaled be Bignum.decbn_copy(da, dca)
    If scaled is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    While scaled_count is less than target_digits:
        Let bigger_buf be Bignum.decbn_alloc(scaled_count plus 3)
        If bigger_buf is equal to 0:
            Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Let cpi be 0
        While cpi is less than scaled_count:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(bigger_buf, cpi, Memory.memory_get_byte(scaled, cpi))
            Set cpi to cpi plus 1
        End While
        Memory.memory_set_byte(bigger_buf, scaled_count, 0)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(bigger_buf, scaled_count plus 1, 0)
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
        Set scaled to bigger_buf
        Set scaled_count to scaled_count plus 2
        Set scaled_exp to scaled_exp minus 2
    End While
    Note: Ensure exponent is even.
    If scaled_exp minus ((scaled_exp divided by 2) multiplied by 2) is not equal to 0:
        Let bigger_buf2 be Bignum.decbn_alloc(scaled_count plus 2)
        If bigger_buf2 is equal to 0:
            Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
            Return dec128_make_qnan()
        End If
        Let cpi2 be 0
        While cpi2 is less than scaled_count:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(bigger_buf2, cpi2, Memory.memory_get_byte(scaled, cpi2))
            Set cpi2 to cpi2 plus 1
        End While
        Memory.memory_set_byte(bigger_buf2, scaled_count, 0)
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
        Set scaled to bigger_buf2
        Set scaled_count to scaled_count plus 1
        Set scaled_exp to scaled_exp minus 1
    End If

    Note: Initial guess: a buffer of (scaled_count/2)+1 digits all 5s
    Note: gives a value approximately midway between 10^(d/2-1) and 10^(d/2).
    Let guess_count be scaled_count divided by 2
    If guess_count is less than 1:
        Set guess_count to 1
    End If
    Let guess be Bignum.decbn_alloc(guess_count plus 2)
    If guess is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_byte(guess, 0, 1)
    Let gi be 1
    While gi is less than guess_count:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(guess, gi, 0)
        Set gi to gi plus 1
    End While

    Note: Newton iteration: x_new = (x + scaled / x) / 2 with monotonic-
    Note: decrease termination.
    Let iter be 0
    Let done be 0
    While done is equal to 0:
        If iter is greater than 200:
            Set done to 1
        Otherwise:
            Let q_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
            Let r_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
            Let r_out_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
            If q_count_ptr is equal to 0:
                Set done to 1
                Set iter to 999
            Otherwise:
                If r_count_ptr is equal to 0:
                    Layout.deallocate(q_count_ptr)
                    Set done to 1
                    Set iter to 999
                Otherwise:
                    If r_out_ptr is equal to 0:
                        Layout.deallocate(q_count_ptr)
                        Layout.deallocate(r_count_ptr)
                        Set done to 1
                        Set iter to 999
                    Otherwise:
                        __store(r_out_ptr, 0, 0)
                        Let div_quot be Bignum.decbn_div_mod(scaled, scaled_count, guess, guess_count, q_count_ptr, r_count_ptr, r_out_ptr)
                        Let dq_count be __load(q_count_ptr, 0)
                        Let dr_buf be __load(r_out_ptr, 0)
                        Layout.deallocate(q_count_ptr)
                        Layout.deallocate(r_count_ptr)
                        Layout.deallocate(r_out_ptr)
                        If dr_buf is not equal to 0:
                            Bignum.decbn_free(dr_buf)
                        End If
                        If div_quot is equal to 0:
                            Set done to 1
                        Otherwise:
                            Note: Add guess + div_quot.
                            Let add_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
                            If add_count_ptr is equal to 0:
                                Bignum.decbn_free(div_quot)
                                Set done to 1
                            Otherwise:
                                Let sum be Bignum.decbn_add_magnitude(guess, guess_count, div_quot, dq_count, add_count_ptr)
                                Let sum_count be __load(add_count_ptr, 0)
                                Layout.deallocate(add_count_ptr)
                                Bignum.decbn_free(div_quot)
                                If sum is equal to 0:
                                    Set done to 1
                                Otherwise:
                                    Note: Divide sum by 2.
                                    Let two_buf be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
                                    If two_buf is equal to 0:
                                        Bignum.decbn_free(sum)
                                        Set done to 1
                                    Otherwise:
                                        Memory.memory_set_byte(two_buf, 0, 2)
                                        Let nq_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
                                        Let nr_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
                                        Let nr_out_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
                                        If nq_count_ptr is equal to 0:
                                            Bignum.decbn_free(sum)
                                            Bignum.decbn_free(two_buf)
                                            Set done to 1
                                        Otherwise:
                                            If nr_count_ptr is equal to 0:
                                                Layout.deallocate(nq_count_ptr)
                                                Bignum.decbn_free(sum)
                                                Bignum.decbn_free(two_buf)
                                                Set done to 1
                                            Otherwise:
                                                If nr_out_ptr is equal to 0:
                                                    Layout.deallocate(nq_count_ptr)
                                                    Layout.deallocate(nr_count_ptr)
                                                    Bignum.decbn_free(sum)
                                                    Bignum.decbn_free(two_buf)
                                                    Set done to 1
                                                Otherwise:
                                                    __store(nr_out_ptr, 0, 0)
                                                    Let new_guess be Bignum.decbn_div_mod(sum, sum_count, two_buf, 1, nq_count_ptr, nr_count_ptr, nr_out_ptr)
                                                    Let ng_count be __load(nq_count_ptr, 0)
                                                    Let nr_buf be __load(nr_out_ptr, 0)
                                                    Layout.deallocate(nq_count_ptr)
                                                    Layout.deallocate(nr_count_ptr)
                                                    Layout.deallocate(nr_out_ptr)
                                                    Bignum.decbn_free(sum)
                                                    Bignum.decbn_free(two_buf)
                                                    If nr_buf is not equal to 0:
                                                        Bignum.decbn_free(nr_buf)
                                                    End If
                                                    If new_guess is equal to 0:
                                                        Set done to 1
                                                    Otherwise:
                                                        Let cmp_ng be Bignum.decbn_compare_magnitude(new_guess, ng_count, guess, guess_count)
                                                        If cmp_ng is greater than or equal to 0:
                                                            Bignum.decbn_free(new_guess)
                                                            Set done to 1
                                                        Otherwise:
                                                            Bignum.decbn_free(guess)
                                                            Set guess to new_guess
                                                            Set guess_count to ng_count
                                                            Set iter to iter plus 1
                                                        End If
                                                    End If
                                                End If
                                            End If
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Note: guess = floor(sqrt(scaled)). Compute (guess+1)^2 to determine
    Note: rounding direction. For correctness we use the digit-buffer
    Note: sticky-bit approach: the round-to-nearest of integer-sqrt is
    Note: itself well-defined per Knuth TAOCP Vol 2 4.3.1.
    Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)

    Let result_exp be scaled_exp divided by 2
    Return dec128_round_finite(0, guess, guess_count, result_exp, rounding_mode)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Conversions
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_from_integer" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Exact conversion from Integer. Integer is at most 18 digits which
    fits comfortably within DEC128_PRECISION = 34, so no rounding is
    needed for any Integer input.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Sign extract, magnitude, build digit buffer via decbn_from_integer,
    wrap as unpacked Decimal128.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(log10 |value|).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let sign be 0
    Let mag be value
    If mag is less than 0:
        Set sign to 1
        Set mag to 0 minus mag
    End If
    If mag is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_zero(0)
    End If
    Let cnt_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If cnt_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Let buf be Bignum.decbn_from_integer(mag, cnt_ptr)
    Let cnt be __load(cnt_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(cnt_ptr)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Return dec128_unpacked_create(sign, DEC128_KIND_FINITE, buf, cnt, 0)
End Process

Process called "dec128_to_integer" takes a as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Decimal128 to Integer with the requested rounding mode. Values
    exceeding Integer range return 0 (caller must check magnitude).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Adjust digit buffer by exponent (append zeros for positive exp,
    truncate-and-round for negative exp). Pack first 18 digits via
    decbn_to_integer_capped.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(|exp|).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Overflow returns 0 sentinel.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    If ka is not equal to DEC128_KIND_FINITE:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    If da is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Adjust digit buffer to integer position.
    Let work_buf be Bignum.decbn_copy(da, dca)
    If work_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let work_count be dca

    If ea is greater than 0:
        Note: Append ea zero digits.
        Let new_count be work_count plus ea
        Let bigger be Bignum.decbn_alloc(new_count plus 1)
        If bigger is equal to 0:
            Bignum.decbn_free(work_buf)
            Return 0
        End If
        Let ci be 0
        While ci is less than work_count:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(bigger, ci, Memory.memory_get_byte(work_buf, ci))
            Set ci to ci plus 1
        End While
        Let zi be 0
        While zi is less than ea:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(bigger, work_count plus zi, 0)
            Set zi to zi plus 1
        End While
        Bignum.decbn_free(work_buf)
        Set work_buf to bigger
        Set work_count to new_count
    End If

    If ea is less than 0:
        Let neg_e be 0 minus ea
        If neg_e is greater than or equal to work_count:
            Bignum.decbn_free(work_buf)
            Return 0
        End If
        Note: Truncate (and round) the trailing neg_e digits.
        Let kept_count be work_count minus neg_e
        Let round_digit be Memory.memory_get_byte(work_buf, kept_count)
        Let sticky be 0
        Let st_i be kept_count plus 1
        While st_i is less than work_count:
            If Memory.memory_get_byte(work_buf, st_i) is not equal to 0:
                Set sticky to 1
                Set st_i to work_count
            Otherwise:
                Set st_i to st_i plus 1
            End If
        End While
        Let round_up be 0
        If rounding_mode is equal to DEC128_ROUND_HALF_EVEN:
            If round_digit is greater than 5:
                Set round_up to 1
            Otherwise:
                If round_digit is equal to 5:
                    If sticky is equal to 1:
                        Set round_up to 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Let last_kept be Memory.memory_get_byte(work_buf, kept_count minus 1)
                        If last_kept is not equal to ((last_kept divided by 2) multiplied by 2):
                            Set round_up to 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If rounding_mode is equal to DEC128_ROUND_HALF_UP:
            If round_digit is greater than or equal to 5:
                Set round_up to 1
            End If
        End If
        If rounding_mode is equal to DEC128_ROUND_TOWARD_POS:
            If sa is equal to 0:
                If round_digit is greater than 0:
                    Set round_up to 1
                End If
                If sticky is equal to 1:
                    Set round_up to 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If rounding_mode is equal to DEC128_ROUND_TOWARD_NEG:
            If sa is equal to 1:
                If round_digit is greater than 0:
                    Set round_up to 1
                End If
                If sticky is equal to 1:
                    Set round_up to 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If round_up is equal to 1:
            Let carry be 1
            Let cp be kept_count minus 1
            While cp is greater than or equal to 0:
                If carry is equal to 0:
                    Set cp to -1
                Otherwise:
                    Let d be Memory.memory_get_byte(work_buf, cp)
                    Set d to d plus 1
                    If d is equal to 10:
                        Memory.memory_set_byte(work_buf, cp, 0)
                        Set carry to 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Memory.memory_set_byte(work_buf, cp, d)
                        Set carry to 0
                    End If
                    Set cp to cp minus 1
                End If
            End While
            If carry is equal to 1:
                Let r2 be kept_count minus 1
                While r2 is greater than or equal to 0:
                    Memory.memory_set_byte(work_buf, r2 plus 1, Memory.memory_get_byte(work_buf, r2))
                    Set r2 to r2 minus 1
                End While
                Memory.memory_set_byte(work_buf, 0, 1)
                Set kept_count to kept_count plus 1
            End If
        End If
        Set work_count to kept_count
    End If

    Let result be Bignum.decbn_to_integer_capped(work_buf, work_count, 18)
    Bignum.decbn_free(work_buf)
    If sa is equal to 1:
        Return 0 minus result
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: String I/O
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_from_string" takes s as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parses a Decimal128 from a null-terminated ASCII string per
    IEEE 754-2008 Section 5.12.2. Uses the digit-buffer parser
    decbn_from_string for the coefficient.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Skip whitespace.
    2. Parse sign.
    3. Handle Inf / NaN keywords.
    4. Parse the integer-then-fractional digit run via two calls to
       a digit accumulator (the bignum module's parser captures all
       digits without precision limit).
    5. Parse optional exponent.
    6. Build the unpacked triple and round.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Single-pass over the input.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Out-of-range exponents are clamped during the final rounding.
    @End Security_Scope

    If s is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Let pos be 0
    Let scanning_ws be 1
    While scanning_ws is equal to 1:
        Let bws be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
        If bws is equal to 32:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        Otherwise:
            If bws is equal to 9:
                Set pos to pos plus 1
            Otherwise:
                If bws is equal to 10:
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    If bws is equal to 13:
                        Set pos to pos plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set scanning_ws to 0
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Let sign be 0
    Let bsign be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
    If bsign is equal to 45:
        Set sign to 1
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If
    If bsign is equal to 43:
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If

    Let bi1 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
    Let bi2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos plus 1)
    Let bi3 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos plus 2)
    Let is_inf be 0
    If bi1 is equal to 73:
        If bi2 is equal to 110:
            If bi3 is equal to 102:
                Set is_inf to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If bi1 is equal to 105:
        If bi2 is equal to 110:
            If bi3 is equal to 102:
                Set is_inf to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If is_inf is equal to 1:
        Return dec128_make_infinity(sign)
    End If

    Let bn1 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
    Let bn2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos plus 1)
    Let bn3 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos plus 2)
    Let is_qnan be 0
    If bn1 is equal to 78:
        If bn2 is equal to 97:
            If bn3 is equal to 78:
                Set is_qnan to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If bn1 is equal to 110:
        If bn2 is equal to 97:
            If bn3 is equal to 110:
                Set is_qnan to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If is_qnan is equal to 1:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Note: Scan for the digit run (integer + fractional parts).
    Note: We track the dot position and accumulate digits into a buffer.
    Let digit_capacity be 128
    Let digit_buf be Bignum.decbn_alloc(digit_capacity)
    If digit_buf is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Let dc be 0
    Let leading_zero be 1
    Let frac_digits be 0
    Let saw_dot be 0
    Let saw_digit be 0
    Let scanning be 1

    While scanning is equal to 1:
        Let bd be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
        If bd is equal to 46:
            If saw_dot is equal to 1:
                Set scanning to 0
            Otherwise:
                Set saw_dot to 1
                Set pos to pos plus 1
            End If
        Otherwise:
            If bd is greater than or equal to 48:
                If bd is less than or equal to 57:
                    Let digit_value be bd minus 48
                    If leading_zero is equal to 1:
                        If digit_value is not equal to 0:
                            If dc is less than digit_capacity:
                                Memory.memory_set_byte(digit_buf, dc, digit_value)
                                Set dc to dc plus 1
                            End If
                            Set leading_zero to 0
                        End If
                    Otherwise:
                        If dc is less than digit_capacity:
                            Memory.memory_set_byte(digit_buf, dc, digit_value)
                            Set dc to dc plus 1
                        End If
                    End If
                    If saw_dot is equal to 1:
                        Set frac_digits to frac_digits plus 1
                    End If
                    Set saw_digit to 1
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set scanning to 0
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Set scanning to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While

    If saw_digit is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(digit_buf)
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    If dc is equal to 0:
        Note: All digits were leading zeros. The value is zero.
        Memory.memory_set_byte(digit_buf, 0, 0)
        Set dc to 1
    End If

    Let exp_val be 0
    Let bexp be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
    Let exp_marker_seen be 0
    If bexp is equal to 101:
        Set exp_marker_seen to 1
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If
    If bexp is equal to 69:
        Set exp_marker_seen to 1
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If
    If exp_marker_seen is equal to 1:
        Let exp_sign be 0
        Let bs2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
        If bs2 is equal to 45:
            Set exp_sign to 1
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        End If
        If bs2 is equal to 43:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        End If
        Let scanning_exp be 1
        While scanning_exp is equal to 1:
            Let be2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
            If be2 is greater than or equal to 48:
                If be2 is less than or equal to 57:
                    Set exp_val to (exp_val multiplied by 10) plus (be2 minus 48)
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set scanning_exp to 0
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Set scanning_exp to 0
            End If
        End While
        If exp_sign is equal to 1:
            Set exp_val to 0 minus exp_val
        End If
    End If

    Let final_exp be exp_val minus frac_digits
    Return dec128_round_finite(sign, digit_buf, dc, final_exp, DEC128_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
End Process

Process called "dec128_to_string" takes a as Integer, buffer as Integer, buffer_size as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes a canonical Decimal128 string per IEEE 754-2008 Section
    5.12.2 into the caller's buffer. Worst case is
    "-9999999999999999999999999999999999E-6176\0" = ~42 bytes; require
    buffer_size >= 48.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Sign, NaN/Inf check, then digit buffer copy and 'E' + exponent.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(digit_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Insufficient buffer returns 0 with no writes.
    @End Security_Scope

    If buffer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If buffer_size is less than 48:
        Return 0
    End If
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let pos be 0
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_QNAN:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 0, 78)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 1, 97)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 2, 78)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 3, 0)
        Return 3
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_SNAN:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 0, 115)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 1, 78)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 2, 97)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 3, 78)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 4, 0)
        Return 4
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 0, 73)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 1, 110)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 2, 102)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 3, 0)
        Return 3
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 0, 45)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 1, 73)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 2, 110)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 3, 102)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 4, 0)
        Return 4
    End If

    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    If sa is equal to 1:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, pos, 45)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If

    If dca is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, pos, 48)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Let k be 0
        While k is less than dca:
            Let d be Memory.memory_get_byte(da, k)
            Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, pos, d plus 48)
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set k to k plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, pos, 69)
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let e_work be ea
    If e_work is less than 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, pos, 45)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Set e_work to 0 minus e_work
    End If
    If e_work is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, pos, 48)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    Otherwise:
        Let e_buf be Layout.allocate(16)
        If e_buf is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let e_pos be 0
        While e_work is greater than 0:
            Let ed be e_work minus ((e_work divided by 10) multiplied by 10)
            Memory.memory_set_byte(e_buf, e_pos, ed plus 48)
            Set e_pos to e_pos plus 1
            Set e_work to e_work divided by 10
        End While
        Let m be e_pos minus 1
        While m is greater than or equal to 0:
            Let ed2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(e_buf, m)
            Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, pos, ed2)
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set m to m minus 1
        End While
        Layout.deallocate(e_buf)
    End If

    Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, pos, 0)
    Return pos
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BID interchange encoding/decoding (128-bit, returned as two-word pair)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dec128_encode_bid" takes a as Integer, out_high_ptr as Integer, out_low_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Encodes a Decimal128 unpacked triple into the BID-128 interchange
    form per IEEE 754-2008 Section 3.5.2. Output is a 128-bit value
    split across two 64-bit Integer words (high, low). The caller
    provides storage pointers; this routine writes the result and
    returns 1 on success, 0 on failure.

    BID-128 layout:
        bit 127:        sign
        bits 126..110:  combination (17 bits)
        bits 109..0:    coefficient continuation

    Per Table 3.5: the combination encodes biased_exp + the implicit
    leading digit pattern. For Decimal128 the natural exponent width
    is 14 bits (biased 0..12287) and the coefficient is 113 bits
    binary (34 decimal digits up to ~10^34 < 2^113).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Special values (NaN/Inf) encoded via combination top bits.
    2. Finite: convert digit buffer to binary, then compose sign,
       biased_exp, and coefficient into the two-word layout.

    To avoid 128-bit binary arithmetic (which the bootstrap stage
    cannot express directly) we encode the coefficient as a
    decimal-encoded big-endian byte string and write the metadata
    around it. This is a deliberate simplification: the BID encoding
    here keeps the digit-buffer form alongside the bit-level header.
    A future revision will compute the full 113-bit binary
    coefficient when the multi-precision binary infrastructure is
    online.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(digit_count) for the coefficient encoding step.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    out_high_ptr and out_low_ptr must point at writable Integer
    storage.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is equal to 0:
        If out_high_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_high_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        If out_low_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_low_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If out_high_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If out_low_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let sign_bit be 0
    If sa is equal to 1:
        Set sign_bit to -9223372036854775808
    End If

    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_POS_INF:
        __store(out_high_ptr, 0, sign_bit bitwise or 8646911284551352320)
        __store(out_low_ptr, 0, 0)
        Return 1
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_NEG_INF:
        __store(out_high_ptr, 0, sign_bit bitwise or 8646911284551352320)
        __store(out_low_ptr, 0, 0)
        Return 1
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_QNAN:
        __store(out_high_ptr, 0, sign_bit bitwise or 8935141660703064064)
        __store(out_low_ptr, 0, 0)
        Return 1
    End If
    If ka is equal to DEC128_KIND_SNAN:
        __store(out_high_ptr, 0, sign_bit bitwise or 9079256848778952704)
        __store(out_low_ptr, 0, 0)
        Return 1
    End If

    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let biased be ea plus DEC128_BIAS
    If biased is less than 0:
        Set biased to 0
    End If
    If biased is greater than DEC128_MAX_BIASED_EXP:
        Set biased to DEC128_MAX_BIASED_EXP
    End If

    Note: Place biased exponent in bits 126..113 (high word bits 62..49).
    Let exp_field be biased shifted left by 49
    Let high_word be sign_bit bitwise or exp_field

    Note: Pack the lower 18 digits of the coefficient as a binary
    Note: integer in the low word, and the upper digits into the high
    Note: word's lower bits. We use decbn_to_integer_capped to extract
    Note: the lowest 18 digits, then re-pack the high digits separately.
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let low_word be 0
    If da is not equal to 0:
        If dca is less than or equal to 18:
            Set low_word to Bignum.decbn_to_integer_capped(da, dca, 18)
        Otherwise:
            Note: Split: high digits = dca - 18, then low digits = 18.
            Note: For 34-digit decimal, the high portion is 16 digits.
            Let high_part_count be dca minus 18
            Let high_part_value be Bignum.decbn_to_integer_capped(da, high_part_count, 18)
            Note: Extract low 18 digits.
            Let low_buf be Bignum.decbn_alloc(20)
            If low_buf is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Let li be 0
            While li is less than 18:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(low_buf, li, Memory.memory_get_byte(da, high_part_count plus li))
                Set li to li plus 1
            End While
            Set low_word to Bignum.decbn_to_integer_capped(low_buf, 18, 18)
            Bignum.decbn_free(low_buf)
            Set high_word to high_word bitwise or high_part_value
        End If
    End If

    __store(out_high_ptr, 0, high_word)
    __store(out_low_ptr, 0, low_word)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "dec128_decode_bid" takes high_word as Integer, low_word as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Decodes a 128-bit BID pair into an unpacked Decimal128 triple.
    Inverse of dec128_encode_bid.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Extract sign from high_word bit 63.
    2. Check combination bits 62..58 for special values.
    3. Extract biased exponent and coefficient digits.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Bitwise extraction; one digit-buffer allocation.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Garbage input produces a well-formed triple (possibly NaN or
    Inf).
    @End Security_Scope

    Let sign_bit be high_word bitwise and -9223372036854775808
    Let sign be 0
    If sign_bit is not equal to 0:
        Set sign to 1
    End If

    Let combo be (high_word shifted right by 58) bitwise and 31
    If combo is equal to 30:
        Return dec128_make_infinity(sign)
    End If
    If combo is equal to 31:
        Let nan_bit be (high_word shifted right by 57) bitwise and 1
        If nan_bit is equal to 1:
            Return dec128_make_snan()
        End If
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Let biased be (high_word shifted right by 49) bitwise and 16383
    Let exp_val be biased minus DEC128_BIAS

    Note: Reconstruct the 34-digit coefficient: high 16 digits from the
    Note: high_word low bits, low 18 digits from the entire low_word.
    Let high_digits_value be high_word bitwise and 562949953421311
    Let low_digits_value be low_word

    Let cnt_ptr_low be Layout.allocate(8)
    If cnt_ptr_low is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Let low_buf be Bignum.decbn_from_integer(low_digits_value, cnt_ptr_low)
    Let low_cnt be __load(cnt_ptr_low, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(cnt_ptr_low)
    If low_buf is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    If high_digits_value is equal to 0:
        Return dec128_unpacked_create(sign, DEC128_KIND_FINITE, low_buf, low_cnt, exp_val)
    End If

    Let cnt_ptr_high be Layout.allocate(8)
    If cnt_ptr_high is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(low_buf)
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Let high_buf be Bignum.decbn_from_integer(high_digits_value, cnt_ptr_high)
    Let high_cnt be __load(cnt_ptr_high, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(cnt_ptr_high)
    If high_buf is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(low_buf)
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If

    Note: Combine high_buf and low_buf into a single buffer with
    Note: 18 low-position zero-padding for the low portion.
    Let total_count be high_cnt plus 18
    Let combined be Bignum.decbn_alloc(total_count plus 1)
    If combined is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(high_buf)
        Bignum.decbn_free(low_buf)
        Return dec128_make_qnan()
    End If
    Let hi_i be 0
    While hi_i is less than high_cnt:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(combined, hi_i, Memory.memory_get_byte(high_buf, hi_i))
        Set hi_i to hi_i plus 1
    End While
    Note: Right-align low_buf into the next 18 positions of combined.
    Let pad be 18 minus low_cnt
    Let pi be 0
    While pi is less than pad:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(combined, high_cnt plus pi, 0)
        Set pi to pi plus 1
    End While
    Let lo_i be 0
    While lo_i is less than low_cnt:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(combined, high_cnt plus pad plus lo_i, Memory.memory_get_byte(low_buf, lo_i))
        Set lo_i to lo_i plus 1
    End While
    Bignum.decbn_free(high_buf)
    Bignum.decbn_free(low_buf)

    Return dec128_unpacked_create(sign, DEC128_KIND_FINITE, combined, total_count, exp_val)
End Process
